  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Avenor Grasscutter and Beekeeping Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Farmer households, Women, Youth</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Theoretical and hands-on training in beekeeping, grasscutter management and small ruminant production. Training in project management and record keeping. Training in compost preparation and agro forestry. Training on leadership skills development.  Training on the 12 HPI cornerstones. Training on gender equity. HIV/AIDS awareness creation. Farmer to farmer visitation.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project, located about 100 miles southeast of the capital Accra, will directly assist 164 families in 10 nearby communities. Twenty-seven of the families will each receive five grasscutters and a cage, while the remaining 137 families will each receive five beehives and beekeeping equipment. Each participating family will also receive 20 laying chickens, and the 10 project communities will share 1,000 tree seedlings. All project beneficiaries will receive training in grasscutter production or beekeeping, poultry production, and agroforestry, as well as HIV/AIDS prevention, gender equity, bushfire prevention and agribusiness development. Another 328 families will benefit through &#x201C;passing on the gift.&quot;</narrative>
  </description>
